<CENTER><b><i>Claims</b></i></CENTER> <HR> <BR><BR>Having thus described the preferred embodiments, the invention is now claimed to be: <BR><BR>1.  An intracellular flush solution for preserving an organ for transplantation, comprising:
<BR><BR>(a) between about 1.54 and 2.56 grams per liter of KH.sub.2 PO.sub.4 ;
<BR><BR>(b) between about 7.38 and 12.2 grams per liter of K.sub.2 HPO.sub.4 ;
<BR><BR>(c) between about 0.84 and 1.40 grams per liter of KCl;
<BR><BR>(d) between about 0.63 and 1.05 grams per liter of NaHCO.sub.3 ;
<BR><BR>(e) between about 0 and 2.87 grams per liter of KHCO.sub.3 ;
<BR><BR>(f) between about 20 and 37 grams per liter of mannitol;
<BR><BR>(g) between about 0 and 4.62 grams per liter of MgSO.sub.4 ;
<BR><BR>(h) between about 0 and 0.4 meq/ml of MgCl.sub.2 ;
<BR><BR>(i) between about 0.75 and 1.25 grams per liter of adenosine;
<BR><BR>(j) between about 0 and 0.125 grams per liter of allopurinol;  and,
<BR><BR>(k) between about 0 and 1.0 grams per liter of verapamil.
<BR><BR>2.  The intracellular flush solution of claim 1, wherein said mannitol is present in an amount sufficient to adjust the osmolality of the solution to a value between about 255 and 425 mOsm/Kg.
<BR><BR>3.  An intracellular flush solution for preserving an organ for transplantation, comprising:
<BR><BR>(a) between about 1.54 and 2.56 grams per liter of KH.sub.2 PO.sub.4 ;
<BR><BR>(b) between about 7.38 and 12.2 grams per liter of K.sub.2 HPO.sub.4 ;
<BR><BR>(c) between about 0.84 and 1.40 grams per liter of KCl;
<BR><BR>(d) between about 0.63 and 1.05 grams per liter of NaHCO.sub.3 ;
<BR><BR>(e) between about 0 and 2.87 grams per liter of KHCO.sub.3 ;
<BR><BR>(f) between about 20 and 37 grams per liter of mannitol;
<BR><BR>(g) between about 0.2 and 0.4 meq/ml of MgCl.sub.2 ;
<BR><BR>(h) between about 0.75 and 1.25 grams per liter of adenosine;
<BR><BR>(i) between about 0 and 0.125 grams per liter of allopurinol;  and,
<BR><BR>(j) between about 0 and 1.0 grams per liter of verapamil.
<BR><BR>4.  An intracellular flush solution for preserving an organ for transplantation comprising: about 2.05 grams per liter KH.sub.2 PO.sub.4 ;  about 9.7 grams per liter K.sub.2 HPO.sub.4 ;  about 1.12 grams per liter KCl;  about 0.84 grams per liter
NaHCO.sub.3 ;  about 25.0 grams per liter mannitol;  about 3.7 grams per liter MgSO.sub.4 ;  and about 1.0 grams per liter adenosine.
<BR><BR>5.  An intracellular flush solution for preserving an organ for transplantation comprising: about 2.05 grams per liter KH.sub.2 PO.sub.4 ;  about 9.7 grams per liter K.sub.2 HPO.sub.4 ;  about 1.12 grams per liter KCl;  about 0.84 grams per liter
NaHCO.sub.3 ;  about 2.3 grams per liter KHCO.sub.3 ;  about 25.0 grams per liter mannitol;  about 3.7 grams per liter MgSO.sub.4 ;  about 1.0 grams per liter adenosine;  about 0.1 grams per liter allopurinol;  and, about 0.007 verapamil.
<BR><BR>6.  An intracellular flush solution for preserving an organ for transplantation comprising:
<BR><BR>(a) a modified Collins C-2 solution containing about 2.05 grams per liter of KH.sub.2 PO.sub.4 ;  about 9.70 grams per liter K.sub.2 HPO.sub.4, about 1.12 grams per liter KCl;  and, about 0.84 grams per liter NaHCO.sub.3 ;
<BR><BR>(b) about 25 grams per liter mannitol;
<BR><BR>(c) about 3.7 grams per liter MgSO.sub.4 ;  and,
<BR><BR>(d) about 1.0 grams per liter adenosine.
<BR><BR>7.  An intracellular flush solution for preserving an organ for transplantation comprising:
<BR><BR>(a) a modified Collins C-2 solution containing about 2.05 grams per liter of KH.sub.2 PO.sub.4 ;  about 9.70 grams per liter K.sub.2 HPO.sub.4, about 1.12 grams per liter KCl;  and, about 0.84 grams per liter NaHCO.sub.3 ;
<BR><BR>(b) about 25 grams per liter mannitol;
<BR><BR>(c) about 3.7 grams per liter MgSO.sub.4 ;
<BR><BR>(d) about 1.0 grams per liter adenosine;
<BR><BR>(e) about 2.3 grams per liter KHCO.sub.3 ;
<BR><BR>(f) about 0.1 grams per liter allopurinol;  and,
<BR><BR>(g) about 0.007 grams per liter verapamil.
<BR><BR>8.  An intracellular flush solution for preserving an organ for transplantation comprising a modified Collins C-2 solution devoid of glucose and MgSO.sub.4 ;  and, about 25 grams per liter mannitol;  about 3.7 grams per liter MgSO.sub.4 ;  and
about 1.0 grams per liter adenosine.
<BR><BR>9.  An intracellular flush solution for preserving an organ for transplantation comprising a modified Collins C-2 solution devoid of glucose and MgSO.sub.4 ;  and, about 25 grams per liter mannitol;  about 3.7 grams per liter MgSO.sub.4 ;  about
1.0 grams per liter adenosine;  about 2.3 grams per liter KHCO.sub.3 ;  about 0.1 grams per liter allopurinol;  and, about 0.007 grams per liter verapamil.
<BR><BR>10.  A method for preserving an organ for transplantation comprising flushing the organ to be transplanted with an intracellular flush solution comprising:
<BR><BR>(a) between about 1.54 and 2.56 grams per liter of KH.sub.2 PO.sub.4 ;
<BR><BR>(b) between about 7.38 and 12.2 grams per liter of K.sub.2 HPO.sub.4 ;
<BR><BR>(c) between about 0.84 and 1.40 grams per liter of KCl;
<BR><BR>(d) between about 0.63 and 1.05 grams per liter of NaHCO.sub.3 ;
<BR><BR>(e) between about 0 and 2.87 grams per liter of KHCO.sub.3 ;
<BR><BR>(f) between about 20 and 37 grams per liter of mannitol;
<BR><BR>(g) between about 2.77 and 4.62 grams per liter of MgSO.sub.4 ;
<BR><BR>(h) between about 0.75 and 1.25 grams per liter of adenosine;
<BR><BR>(i) between about 0 and 0.125 grams per liter of allopurinol;  and,
<BR><BR>(j) between about 0 and 1.0 grams per liter of verapamil.
<BR><BR>11.  A method for preserving an organ for transplantation comprising flushing the organ to be transplanted with an intracellular flush solution comprising:
<BR><BR>(a) between about 1.54 and 2.56 grams per liter of KH.sub.2 PO.sub.4 ;
<BR><BR>(b) between about 7.38 and 12.2 grams per liter of K.sub.2 HPO.sub.4 ;
<BR><BR>(c) between about 0.84 and 1.40 grams per liter of KCl;
<BR><BR>(d) between about 0.63 and 1.05 grams per liter of NaHCO.sub.3 ;
<BR><BR>(e) between about 0 and 2.87 grams per liter of KHCO.sub.3 ;
<BR><BR>(f) between about 20 and 37 grams per liter of mannitol;
<BR><BR>(g) between about 0.2 and 0.4 meq/ml of MgCl.sub.2 ;
<BR><BR>(h) between about 0.75 and 1.25 grams per liter of adenosine;
<BR><BR>(i) between about 0 and 0.125 grams per liter of allopurinol;  and,
<BR><BR>(j) between about 0 and 1.0 grams per liter of verapamil.
<BR><BR>12.  A method for preserving an organ for transplantation comprising flushing the organ to be transplanted with an intracellular flush solution comprising about 2.05 grams per liter KH.sub.2 PO.sub.4 ;  about 9.7 grams per liter K.sub.2 HPO.sub.4
;  about 1.12 grams per liter KCl;  about 0.84 grams per liter NaHCO.sub.3 ;  about 25.0 grams per liter mannitol;  about 3.7 grams per liter MgSO.sub.4 ;  and about 1.0 grams per liter adenosine.
<BR><BR>13.  A method for preserving an organ for transplantation comprising flushing the organ to be transplanted with an intracellular flush solution comprising about 2.05 grams per liter KH.sub.2 PO.sub.4 ;  about 9.7 grams per liter K.sub.2 HPO.sub.4
;  about 1.12 grams per liter KCl;  about 0.84 grams per liter NaHCO.sub.3 ;  about 2.3 grams per liter KHCO.sub.3 ;  about 25.0 grams per liter mannitol;  about 3.7 grams per liter MgSO.sub.4 ;  about 1.0 grams per liter adenosine;  about 0.1 grams per
liter allopurinol;  and, about 0.007 verapamil.
<BR><BR>14.  A method for preserving an organ for transplantation comprising flushing the organ to be transplanted with an intracellular flush solution comprising:
<BR><BR>(a) a modified Collins C-2 solution containing about 2.05 grams per liter of KH.sub.2 PO.sub.4 ;  about 9.70 grams per liter K.sub.2 HPO.sub.4, about 1.12 grams per liter KCl;  and, about 0.84 grams per liter NaHCO.sub.3 ;
<BR><BR>(b) about 25 grams per liter mannitol;
<BR><BR>(c) about 3.7 grams per liter MgSO.sub.4 ;  and,
